Deputy President David Mabuza, has arrived in Sudan on his second leg of the member states of the Intergovernmental Authority on Development. He was received by Vice President Lieutenant-General Bakri Hassan Salih at the Khartoum International Airport last night.   As Special Envoy, the Deputy President concluded his two-day visit to South Sudan on Monday.   In Sudan Mabuza Is expected to meet with Riek Machar, a former South Sudan Vice President who turned into opposition after fallout with President Salva Kiir and is now his rival. He will also meet Sudan President Omar Al-Bashir. Later Tuesday afternoon he will meet with President Yoweri Museveni in Uganda where half a million South Sudan refugees have fled during the civil war. WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: 